matomo (4.9.0-1) stable; urgency=high

  * Releasing Matomo 4.9.0
  * New segments for 'Ecommerce Order Revenue' and 'Revenue left in
    cart' [by @peterhashair] (Closes: #15985)
  * Detect when the website is a Single Page App (SPA) or a Progressive
    Web App (PWA) and link to the relevant guide [by @peterhashair]
    (Closes: #18066)
  * Matomo knowledgebase discoverability improvements [by
    @justinvelluppillai] (Closes: #18934)
  * Improve performance in deleteLogDataForDeletedSites when deleting
    data for more than one site (Closes: #18618)
  * Clarify the Newsletter Opt-in message during installation  [by
    @peterhashair] (Closes: #18787)
  * Handle case only file name updates on case insensitive file systems
    [by @bx80, @justinvelluppillai] (Closes: #18865)
  * Fix Sarawak and Terengganu on Visitors Interactive Map Widget [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #19006)
  * Inline Help - show report generation date on "Overview" reports with
    Evolution Graphs [by @peterhashair] (Closes: #18806)
  * Don't log an error when not supported browser is used [by @bx80]
    (Closes: #17738)
  * Don't create test cookies when cookies are disabled [by
    @justinvelluppillai] (Closes: #17892)
  * Set the _pk_id in the past when deleting cookie.  [by
    @aleksijohansson] (Closes: #18902)
  * Remove subtable tooltip if rows are displayed expanded upon search
    [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #18873)
  * Minor performance improvement for archive invalidator [by @tsteur]
    (Closes: #18990)
  * Multi server environment in maintenance mode shouldn't result in 503
    response [by @peterhashair] (Closes: #18054)
  * Prevent archiving of data for time periods that start in the future
    [by @bx80] (Closes: #18790)
  * Apply max execution query time to Live.getCounters API and
    queryAdjacentVisitorId method [by @tsteur] (Closes: #18852)
  * Migrate Dashboard directive/model to VueJS [by @diosmosis] (Closes:
    #18883)
  * Fix PHP8 Trim Error [by @deybhayden, @sgiehl] (Closes: #18903)
  * Migrate custom dimension management [by @diosmosis, @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #18926)
  * Migrate LanguagesManager to VueJS [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #18931)
  * Migrate live widget refresh to VueJS [by @diosmosis, @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #18932)
  * Migrate multisites plugin components to VueJS [by @diosmosis]
    (Closes: #18939)
  * Rename dimensions and segments with Server time to Site Time/Time in
    UTC [by @AltamashShaikh, @sgiehl] (Closes: #18956)
  * Migrate AnonymizeIpController to VueJS [by @diosmosis, @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #18975)
  * Migrate DoNotTrackPreferenceController to VueJS [by @diosmosis,
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #18989)
  * Fix issue where date ranges might include too many subperiods  [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #18995)
  * Add new option to Matomo Variable to disable browser feature
    detection in Matomo Tag (Closes: #443)
  * Improve tracking capabilities of visibility events [by @tomper00,
    @AltamashShaikh] (Closes: #321)
  * Fix bug preventing "0" value for trigger condition [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #450)
  * Migrate version management to VueJS [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #423)
  * Migrate container management to VueJS [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #424)
  * Add detection for new device type wearables  (Closes: #5316)
  * Introduce browser client hint detection [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #6989)
  * Detect devices for brands: Teclast, Readboy, Vivo, Xiaomi, Conquest,
    Huawei, AllDocube, OPPO, Meizu, Newman, Lava, Hisense [by
    @sanchezzzhak, @sgiehl] (Closes: #7018)
  * Detect new brands Angelcare, Hamlet, Vorcom and Detect devices for
    several existing brands  [by @sanchezzzhak, @sgiehl] (Closes: #7021)
  * Add engine for CCleaner and ToGate [by @liviuconcioiu, @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #7022)
  * Improve version detection for Chrome OS [by @liviuconcioiu,
    @sanchezzzhak] (Closes: #7023)
  * Adds detection for ClearPHONE, Doppio, Jio, Point Mobile, Schok,
    Vios devices, improves detection for Alcatel, Allview, AT&T, Blu,
    Crosscall, Digicel, Hipstreet, Hisense, HTC, Huawei, Hurricane,
    Hyundai, iHunt, Kalley, Kodak, KRIP, LG, Logic, Mione, Motorola,
    OnePlus, OpelMobile, Pantech, Positivo, Quantum, Realme, Sky, TCL,
    Techwood, Tecno Mobile, Tigers, Vivo, Wiko, Wolki, Xiaomi, Yes,
    Yezz, ZTE devices, adds detection for ClearOS Mobile [by
    @liviuconcioiu, @sanchezzzhak] (Closes: #7025)
