matomo (4.1.1-1) stable; urgency=high

  * Releasing Matomo 4.1.1
  * Have a report description for every report [by @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #16792)
  * Admin menu should be collapsible for admins/super users [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #16793)
  * Add feature to ignore traffic of Cloud providers - prevent spam
    tracking (Closes: #16794)
  * Looping with filter_limit and filter_offset does not always get all
    visits [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #16394)
  * Anonymise IP when sending feedback through Matomo UI [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #17052)
  * Add regular expression support to list of user agents to exclude [by
    @nina-py, @diosmosis] (Closes: #16766)
  * Add imprint URL to Template.pageFooter (Closes: #16965)
  * Evolution graphs: "Change period" feature to show historical up to
    the very last period within the selected date range [by @diosmosis]
    (Closes: #14149)
  * Limit max execution time for all SQL queries executed during report
    archiving [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #15241)
  * Remove the incorrect tooltips in Visitors > Overview  [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #16371)
  * File Integrity Issues after Upgrade (Closes: #16938)
  * 4.1.0 Data from "Channel Types" and others are showing Yesterday's
    data while some other part are showing today's data [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #16999)
  * Better fix for climulti segment encoding bug [by @diosmosis]
    (Closes: #17004)
  * Matomo doesn't respect SMTP Encryption Method setting [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #17015)
  * Password recovery SMTP email configuration [by @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #17026)
  * -skip-idsites argument to core:archive works like -force-idsites in
    4.x [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #17074)
  * Use `hiddenkeyword` for Search engines by default (Closes: #16742)
  * Ensure no longer used node module files are removed on update [by
    @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #17059)
  * updates device detector to latest 4.1.0 [by @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #17064)
  * Segmented visitor log does not load any content when the Outlink URL
    or Download URL contains an ampersand [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #11806)
  * going to 'All Websites' dashboard and selecting a date range and
    clicking a site results in error message [by @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #15238)
  * The parameter 'confirmPassword' isn't set in the Request [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #16847)
  * Error when viewing Page performance report with "Date Range" [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #17003)
  * [automatic translation update] Updated 116 strings in 6 languages
    (ru da el zh-tw tr sv) [by @github-actions[bot], @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #17036)
  * [automatic translation update] Updated 73 strings in 34 languages
    (ru de es da pt-br el ro ko bg be zh-cn pt cs vi id ca pl ja it ar
    uk nl nb es-ar fr zh-tw tr tl lv fa sq sr fi sv) [by @github-
    actions[bot], @sgiehl] (Closes: #17065)
  * Text error in German translation -> "oderr" (Closes: #17067)
  * add href in link in update message email [by @aloxe, @diosmosis]
    (Closes: #16661)
  * Let users configure a max actions per visit that should be recorded
    (available in TrackingSpamPrevention plugin) (Closes: #16802)
  * Don't accept files that are bigger than the upload limit when
    uploading plugins [by @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #16849)
  * After updating to 4.0.5, plugin file VisitsByDaysSinceLastVisit.php
    is not deleted [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #16927)
  * Version 4 can break websites with a Content Security Policy [by
    @tsteur] (Closes: #16935)
  * always send an "Accept-Encoding" header with HTTP requests [by
    @Findus23, @diosmosis] (Closes: #17009)
  * Make "Compare To" translatable [by @c960657, @diosmosis] (Closes:
    #17021)
  * Rename piwik to matomo in uninstall script [by @mattab, @diosmosis]
    (Closes: #17061)
  * -force-all-periods is not supported and -force-date-last-n only
    applies to new segments [by @diosmosis, @sgiehl] (Closes: #296)
  * Adds detection for Chim Lrowser [by @liviuconcioiu, @sanchezzzhak]
    (Closes: #6472)
  * Adds detection for PlayFree Browser [by @liviuconcioiu,
    @sanchezzzhak] (Closes: #6473)
  * Adds detection for SFive browser [by @liviuconcioiu, @sanchezzzhak]
    (Closes: #6474)
