    #221)

 -- Matomo Autonomous Build System <nobody@matomo.org>  Sun, 18 Nov 2018 05:06:47 +0000

matomo (3.6.0-1) stable; urgency=high

  * Releasing Matomo 3.6.0
  * Improve User Management and assigning permissions to users [by
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #6187)
  * New setting to disable all outgoing http requests from a Piwik
    server [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #6324)
  * Sessions with more security [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12208)
  * When website has been deleted, we should also delete the raw data
    for this website [by @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12907)
  * Possibility to unsubscribe from Email reports (pdf, html, csv) [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #2197)
  * Split "Social network" as its own referrer type in "All referrers"
    report [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #11102)
  * Compatibility with MySQL Group Replication and MySQL InnoDB Cluster
    [by @Aardvark8, @diosmosis] (Closes: #11885)
  * When a custom segment is used in an API request and
    browser_archiving_disabled_enforce=1, throw an exception explaining
    to create the segment first [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12255)
  * New widget "Generic > Metric" to display any of the metric / KPI
    available in Matomo [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12358)
  * Scalable UX for user management [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #13158)
  * Introducing a new role "write" and possibility to define
    capabilities [by @tsteur, @diosmosis] (Closes: #13163)
  * Implements possibility to unsubscribe from email reports [by
    @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #13214)
  * New system check to Warn users if force_ssl is not yet enabled [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #7279)
  * Show paging and search in the screen 'Manage users' to easily manage
    hundreds of users [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #4474)
  * replace sparkline library with modern equivalent [by @Findus23,
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12066)
  * Geoip2 geolocation lookup is slow (Closes: #12955)
  * Change order of Ecommerce => Products (Closes: #12970)
  * Hide GeoIP2 server module settings by default [by @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #13053)
  * Let super users configure CORS hostnames in the UI [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #13156)
  * Session not invalidated after logout [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #6531)
  * Language selector in top menu does not apply theme color [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #13291)
  * MySQL 5.7.17 compatibility (where group replication enabled by
    default) [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #11596)
  * Allow to provide secondary sort column for reports [by @sgiehl,
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12128)
  * Widget title does not change when switching to related report [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12681)
  * Allow emails to be themed. [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #13223)
  * When a segment is set to "reports are pre-processed" and viewing a
    report which hasn't yet been processed, display a notification [by
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12256)
  * When there is a memory error in core:archive process, have a way to
    see the backtrace [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #13196)
  * Check that all Matomo cookies are set with the Secure flag in the UI
    (Closes: #12841)
  * After clicking "Check for updates" button, the "zen menu" icon is
    displayed twice [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12990)
  * Update cacert.pem (used for validating SSL connections) [by @mattab,
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #13094)
  * Ensure segmented visitor log numeration doesn't break [by @sgiehl,
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #13169)
  * Fix parameter unset and escaping [by @sgiehl, @mattab] (Closes:
    #13240)
  * In the Segmented Visitor Log popover, let me open the Visitor
    Profile [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #7214)
  * Event Value Segment [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12648)
  * GDPR: When consent has been given by a user, set &consent=1 in the
    Tracking API URL [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12834)
  * Show info message in visitor profile if there had been more visits
    than shown in the summary [by @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12863)
  * Console is named Piwik instead of Matomo plus matomo-domain option
    [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12924)
  * Add privacy policy/terms and conditions settings and display in
    bottom of certain pages [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12938)
