 -- Matomo Autonomous Build System <nobody@matomo.org>  Sun, 24 Jun 2018 03:35:23 +0000

matomo (3.5.0-1) stable; urgency=high

  * Releasing Matomo 3.5.0
  * Tracking code could use HTTPS when the Piwik server is configured to
    force SSL connections [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #7366)
  * Make geoip backend work with geoip2 [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #4487)
  * Support for MySQL and SSL Connections (Closes: #7039)
  * GDPR + Add a couple of new platform features especially around
    validating settings [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes: #12558)
  * GDPR - Overview / Info screen (Closes: #12594)
  * GDPR - Right to access data (Closes: #12595)
  * GDPR - Right to erasure or right to be forgotten (Closes: #12596)
  * GDPR - Right to rectification (Closes: #12597)
  * GDPR - The data subject right to restriction of processing / The
    right to withdraw consent (Closes: #12598)
  * GDPR - The right to be informed (Closes: #12599)
  * Matomo Analytics - GDPR Compliance Project (Closes: #12600)
  * Add FAQ for how to use SSL connections to MySQL (Closes: #12636)
  * Personal Data Anonymisation & Removal tool for analytics raw data -
    GDPR compliance (Closes: #12641)
  * Moves various UI tests to their plugins [by @sgiehl] (Closes:
    #12649)
  * iframe opt-in/opt-out code is not properly closed [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #12665)
  * CorePluginsAdmin.setSystemSettings always saves the plugin settings
    for all plugins [by @tsteur] (Closes: #12826)
  * Tracker: Serialization failure: 1213 Deadlock found when trying to
    get lock (Closes: #6398)
  * Row evolution with goal crash [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #11526)
  * Tooltips in conversion overview not working properly [by @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #12676)
  * updates php-di package [by @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12831)
  * GeoIP2 implementation as a plugin [by @sgiehl, @mattab] (Closes:
    #12699)
  * Extra spacing in Visitor log when visits include duplicate actions
    [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12671)
  * Saving plugin settings shows loading/saving indicator for all plugin
    settings (Closes: #12825)
  * Document config setting multi_server_environment=1 for when Piwik is
    deployed on multiple servers (Closes: #10777)
  * New dimensions "Website ID" and "Website name" [by @diosmosis]
    (Closes: #12409)
  * Add minimal first party cookie opt out support to JS tracker [by
    @diosmosis, @mattab] (Closes: #12829)
  * CLI Archiver should not launch daily and weekly/monthly/yearly
    archiving at the same time (Closes: #12718)
  * Visitor log: do not allow to show "all" rows as it can time out [by
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12789)
  * Visitor log should display country/city information without having
    to hover on the country flag [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12015)
  * Fixes regression: rowevolution not working in overlay mode [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12771)
  * Invalid MySQL Version when using MariaDB (Closes: #12772)
  * When setting or resetting User ID, do not update the Visitor ID in
    the first party cookie [by @mattab] (Closes: #12742)
  * Show "Keyword not defined" on hover on the Search engine icons [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12813)
  * IPv6 Geolocation is not working (Closes: #8601)
  * Running "./console core:purge-old-archive-data all" fails on some
    system with [Exception] Date format [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #11778)
  * When a user deletes a site that is currently selected in the URL,
    need to redirect another URL [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12617)
  * Fatal error: Cannot unset string offsets in JqplotDataGenerator [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12627)
  * Overlay API Calls: Not working with View and Admin rights [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12635)
  * In Email reports, Page URLs report append directory root pages with
    /index [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12651)
  * Fix pageview metric so it doesn't include events [by @mattab,
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12700)
  * In Row evolution popover may return "Call to a member function
    toString() on null" [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12734)
  * Fix syntax for 'SHOW COLUMNS FROM' on MySQL 8 [by @jedix, @sgiehl]
    (Closes: #12759)
  * Fixing missing Google indexed pages and Domain age information in
    SEO Rankings widget [by @ecobux, @sgiehl] (Closes: #12821)
  * [automatic translation update] Updated 126 strings in 8 languages
    (de, es, sl, el, pl, sq, tr, zh-tw) [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12704)
  * [automatic translation update] Updated 326 strings in 12 languages
    (da, cs, de, el, fi, pl, pt-br, sq, tr, et, zh-cn, zh-tw) [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12793)
  * [automatic translation update] Updated 16 strings in 4 languages
    (de, el, pl, tr) [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12818)
  * Document heartbeat/"time on page" information for the HTTP Tracking
    API (Closes: #9477)
  * Show information in visitor profile if dataset was "truncated" [by
    @sgiehl, @mattab] (Closes: #12376)
  * Discard idGoal parameter for row evolution in goal visualizations
    [by @sgiehl, @mattab] (Closes: #12378)
  * Option::set() INSERT ... ON DUPLICATE KEY can be slow [by
    @robocoder, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12550)
  * On Azure fallback to "select @@version" [by @robocoder, @mattab]
    (Closes: #12551)
  * Do not run the same archive command twice [by @tsteur, @mattab]
    (Closes: #12702)
  * Added new event to add stylesheets [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes:
    #12705)
  * During core:archive when a day or period archiving fails for a
    website, abort the website archiving [by @mattab] (Closes: #12708)
  * Enable LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE for PHP >= 5.6.17 when mysqlnd is
    used. [by @MichaelHeerklotz, @diosmosis, @mattab] (Closes: #12710)
  * Make sure core:archive terminates when all initial websites have
    been processed [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes: #12716)
  * Log a job ID for cli commands [by @tsteur, @diosmosis] (Closes:
    #12717)
  * piwikUrl.getSearchParam() should not set an empty URL value [by
    @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes: #12728)
  * When invalidating a websites report, allow plugins to invalidate
    additional sites automatically [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes:
    #12729)
  * Escape ampersands in tracker URLs [by @c960657, @mattab] (Closes:
    #12731)
  * This addresses the various dead lock issues when using transactions
    and multiple recorders. [by @kachenjr, @mattab] (Closes: #12733)
  * Aggregate 500 events in a sub-table instead of 100 [by @mattab,
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12741)
  * Add possibility to let a plugin generator define the translation key
    [by @tsteur] (Closes: #12746)
  * Add Common::stripHeader() [by @c960657, @mattab] (Closes: #12748)
  * Faster Real Time Maps [by @sgiehl, @mattab] (Closes: #12752)
  * Empty dashboard page after adding new goal (Closes: #12753)
  * 3rd party cookie visitor ID value should not change over time [by
    @mattab] (Closes: #12755)
  * piwik.js minification: use newer yuicompressor version [by @tsteur,
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12774)
  * Use a higher precision for rates to show more accurate percentage
    values [by @tsteur, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12775)
  * Add new icon rocket, upload and bug [by @tsteur] (Closes: #12776)
  * Prevent tracking failures when invalid goal patterns are defined [by
    @sgiehl, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12787)
  * Validate goal pattern and type in API [by @sgiehl] (Closes: #12788)
  * Add possibility to specify an icon and onclick handler for submenu
    items [by @tsteur] (Closes: #12791)
  * Show number of Goals created in the System summary widget [by
    @sgiehl] (Closes: #12794)
  * Add new embed icon [by @tsteur, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12802)
  * Lower limit from 500 to 400 when searching for visits in GDPR data
    subject search [by @tsteur, @diosmosis] (Closes: #12803)
  * Added new setting field to configure multiple values [by @tsteur,
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12807)
  * Show activity indicator only for plugin settings that is being
    updated [by @tsteur] (Closes: #12828)
  * Update file list that is removed from packages [by @sgiehl,
    @diosmosis] (Closes: #12830)
  * GDPR: Document the new JavaScript tracker methods: requireConsent,
    rememberConsentGiven, forgetConsentGiven, setConsentGiven (Closes:
    #12835)
  * GDPR: The feature to pseudo-anonymise User ID is actually "replacing
    the User ID with a pseudonym" [by @diosmosis] (Closes: #12836)
