  * bump dependency on php to 5.5.9

 -- Aurélien Requiem <aurelien@requiem.fr>  Sun, 15 Jan 2017 15:00:27 +1100

piwik (3.0.0-2) stable; urgency=high

  * renaming specific files
  * added some code to remove Piwik GPG key from /etc/apt/trusted.gpg
  * ship Piwik GPG keys the Debian way. This will allow future upgrades
  * check debian/changelog for 'UNRELEASED' package

 -- Aurélien Requiem <aurelien@requiem.fr>  Sun, 15 Jan 2017 13:55:03 +1100

piwik (3.0.0-1) stable; urgency=high

  * Releasing Piwik 3.0.0
  * Better UI for Piwik 3, more responsive, faster, lots of other fixes
    [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10397)
  * Integer overflow: how to track more than 2 billion actions with
    PiwiK? [by @mattab] (Closes: #3288)
  * API should not prettify labels when requesting period=week with many
    periods [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes: #7480)
  * Provide an API for plugins to display (multiple) reports in a page
    [by @tsteur] (Closes: #7822)
  * Piwik 3 requires PHP 5.5.9 [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10380)
  * Passwords: use better algorithm than md5 hash, use salts and
    maintain BC [by @mneudert, @tsteur] (Closes: #5728)
  * JS Tracker: Enable by default Downloads and Outlinks tracking of
    right and middle mouse clicks [by @tsteur] (Closes: #8224)
  * Schema changes will take place in Piwik 3.0.0 (for tables log_visit,
    log_link_visit_action, log_action) (Closes: #6953)
  * Support for secondary column support and faster datatable sort [by
    @tsteur] (Closes: #8449)
  * On very high traffic Piwik servers, prevent integer overflow by
    making auto_increment fields BIGINT UNSIGNED [by @mattab] (Closes:
    #10548)
  * Drop IE8 support in the user interface[by @tsteur] (Closes: #4620)
  * Extract the first IP from HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR and HTTP_CLIENT_IP
    and HTTP_CF_CONNECTING_IP and HTTP_X_FORWARDED_HOST when there is
    more than one IP [by @mattab] (Closes: #10404)
  * New widget "System summary" [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10353)
  * New widget "System check" [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10354)
  * New widget "new plugins" / Marketplace [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10355)
  * Change font to System Default for better performance and consistency
    [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10446)
  * Updated Piwik 3 icons [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes: #10589)
  * websites management page shouldn't reload entire page when site
    added [by @tsteur] (Closes: #6421)
  * PDF/HTML Reports: Expand Actions reports (and some others) by
    default [by @cbuchli] (Closes: #2137)
  * Improved plugins update API and how plugins define and reuse schema
    migrations [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10028)
  * Make it easier to analyze overlay reports by making overlay bubbles'
    sizes proportional to the metric value [by @phoob, @mattab] (Closes:
    #10447)
  * Apply default filter_limit to all API calls [by @tsteur] (Closes:
    #8458)
  * Numeric value out of range: 1264 Out of range value for column
    'visit_total_actions' at row 1 In query (Closes: #6834)
  * Add a command to generate a UI test for plugins [by @tsteur]
    (Closes: #6741)
  * Websites manager: Add possibility to exclude URL parameters matching
    a regular expressions [by @pafgoncalves, @mattab] (Closes: #10846)
  * Goal reports: for each Device type, Device name, Device model we now
    process Goal conversions, conversion rate and revenue [by @sgiehl,
    @mattab] (Closes: #9777)
  * JavaScript Tracker: new option "Track users with JavaScript
    disabled" and the <noscript> tag is not included by default anymore
    [by @tsteur] (Closes: #10900)
  * Tracking API: when overriding the request datetime with an invalid
    token_auth, don't track the request [by @tsteur, @mattab] (Closes:
    #10890)
  * Super User should not be able to see token_auth of other users
    (Closes: #10938)
  * Updates password/token_auth hashing [by @mneudert, @tsteur] (Closes:
    #10740)
  * Prevent directory listing on apache servers [by @mattab] (Closes:
    #10931)
  * During upgrade, copy & pasting SQL queries manually does complete
    the upgrade -> clarify wording [by @mattab] (Closes: #10720)
